<article class="notes-lab" id="main" data-notes-lab>
  <header class="notes-lab-head">
    <div>
      <h1>Notes lab</h1>
      <p>Edit constellation note text + tune per-class color and glow. Live preview reflects the actual CSS that ships. Export records as JSON or paste-ready CSS overrides.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="notes-lab-actions">
      <button type="button" class="notes-lab-btn" data-action="export-records">copy records JSON</button>
      <button type="button" class="notes-lab-btn" data-action="export-css">copy CSS overrides</button>
      <button type="button" class="notes-lab-btn ghost" data-action="reset-records">reset records</button>
      <button type="button" class="notes-lab-btn ghost" data-action="reset-styles">reset styles</button>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="notes-lab-grid">
    <aside class="notes-lab-sidebar" aria-label="Records">
      <h2>records</h2>
      <ul class="notes-lab-record-list" data-record-list></ul>
    </aside>

    <section class="notes-lab-editor" data-editor aria-live="polite">
      <p class="notes-lab-empty">pick a record on the left to edit</p>
    </section>
  </div>

  <section class="notes-lab-styles" aria-label="Class styles">
    <h2>class styles · color + halo</h2>
    <div class="notes-lab-style-grid" data-style-grid></div>
    <p class="notes-lab-style-help">
      Halo is a layered <code>text-shadow</code>. Each layer = blur radius (rem) + opacity (% of color). Live preview uses these values via injected CSS. <strong>Tip:</strong> match site CSS by reading <code>css/style.css</code> for current values.
    </p>
  </section>

  <p class="notes-lab-status" data-status hidden></p>
</article>

